parameters:
Cors the Wanderer: Thanks to risking my life with all of
you, I've been able to become a big shot within the
organization.

Cors the Wanderer: Although it's unofficial, it seems like
I'll be able to receive a reward from the new king as well.

\CL 【Cors the Wanderer's Aftermath】With the birth of King
Rex, a conflict arises within the Mucos. This conflict will
continue for a long period of time until King Rex takes
action to suppress it.

\CL Cors, who had become a prominent figure within the
organization, is attacked while visiting a grave as part of
his daily routine. Cors is stabbed and pushed into the sea,
and his body is never found.

\CL Although his life and death are unknown, a man
resembling Cors was reportedly sighted on the prostitution
island.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

the room?
Clea (We haven't talked yet, have we?)

3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Clea: Thank you for everything. If you need anything, the
Adventurer's Guild can be both an ally and an enemy.

Cors the Wanderer: I apologize for any fights with you all.
Well, let's maintain a mutually beneficial relationship,
shall we?

Cors the Wanderer: If you have any troublesome matters, feel
free to request my assistance. Well, if there's anything
troublesome on my end as well, let's try to cooperate as
much as possible.

Mage Relm: I'm grateful for being able to study various
things, including things I didn't want to know.

Cors the Wanderer: Hehehe, there must have been good things
about breaking free from a cramped room when becoming an
adult, right?

Mage Relm: Of course! I never imagined that the empire would
be this vast.

Thief Nora: ...There are a lot of things I want to say, but
thank you for keeping your promise with me!

Cors the Wanderer: Well, it's more like the pride of a
hoodlum, you know.

Thief Nora: Next time, I plan to visit the grave. Let's go
together to meet that child.

Priestess Sophia: Hehehe, I have decided to pursue the path
of a priestess once again. I apologize for turning down your
invitations multiple times.

Cors the Wanderer: That's a big loss... With that beauty and
intelligence of yours, you can get anything, you know?

Priestess Sophia: The things I desire are in a place
untouched by praise.
